    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="917"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d917">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2751.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Juárez</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/> (<hi rend="italic"
                                >Juárez</hi>) <hi rend="italic">El Paso, Tex.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Casas Grandes local authorities have declared against the Government. Railroad
                    communications between Juárez and that section abandoned. That portion of my
                    district is reported to be wholly in the control of the anti-Madero followers,
                    who are making demonstrations against the Americans. They have made a demand of
                    the people of the colonies (Mormons) to surrender their firearms (their private
                    property). This demand the Americans will resist, and serious trouble is feared.
                    I will send a written protest to said local officials, using to some extent the
                    language of one year ago as given by the Ambassador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thos. D. Edwards.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
